parameters.name: q
parameters.description: string ( q , name or name_equals required) search over all attributes of a place : place name, country name, continent, admin codes,... ( Important: urlencoded utf8 )

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: string ( q , name or name_equals required) place name only( Important: urlencoded utf8 )

parameters.name: name_equals
parameters.description: string ( q , name or name_equals required) exact place name

parameters.name: name_startsWith
parameters.description: string (optional) place name starts with given characters

parameters.name: maxRows
parameters.description: integer (optional) the maximal number of rows in the document returned by the service. Default is 100, the maximal allowed value is 1000.

parameters.name: startRow
parameters.description: integer (optional) Used for paging results. If you want to get results 30 to 40, use startRow=30 and maxRows=10. Default is 0, the maximal allowed value is 5000 for the free services and 25000 for the premium services

parameters.name: country
parameters.description: string : country code, ISO-3166 (optional) Default is all countries. The country parameter may occur more than once, example: country=FR&country=GP

parameters.name: countryBias
parameters.description: string (option), two letter country code ISO-3166 records from the countryBias are listed first

parameters.name: continentCode
parameters.description: string : continent code : AF,AS,EU,NA,OC,SA,AN (optional) restricts the search for toponym of the given continent.

parameters.name: adminCode1
parameters.description: , adminCode2 , adminCode3 string : admin code (optional) code of administrative subdivision

parameters.name: featureClass
parameters.description: character A , H , L , P , R , S , T , U , V (optional) featureclass(es) (default= all feature classes); this parameter may occur more than once, example: featureClass=P&featureClass=A

parameters.name: featureCode
parameters.description: string (optional) featurecode(s) (default= all feature codes); this parameter may occur more than once, example: featureCode=PPLC&featureCode=PPLX

parameters.name: cities
parameters.description: string (optional) optional filter parameter with three possible values 'cities1000', 'cities5000','cities15000' used to categorize the populated places into three groups according to size/relevance. See the download readme for further infos

parameters.name: lang
parameters.description: string ISO-636 2-letter language code; en , de , fr , it , es ,... (optional) place name and country name will be returned in the specified language. Default is English. Feature classes and codes are only available in English and Bulgarian. Any help in translating is welcome.

parameters.name: type
parameters.description: string xml , json , rdf the format type of the returned document, default = xml

parameters.name: style
parameters.description: string SHORT , MEDIUM , LONG , FULL (optional) verbosity of returned xml document, default = MEDIUM

parameters.name: isNameRequired
parameters.description: boolean (optional) At least one of the search term needs to be part of the place name. Example : A normal search for Berlin will return all places within the state of Berlin. If we only want to find places with 'Berlin' in the name we set the parameter isNameRequired to 'true'. The difference to the name_equals parameter is that this will allow searches for 'Berlin, Germany' as only one search term needs to be part of the name.

parameters.name: tag
parameters.description: string (optional) search for toponyms tagged with the specified tag

parameters.name: operator
parameters.description: string (optional) default is 'AND', with the operator 'OR' not all search terms need to be matched by the response

parameters.name: charset
parameters.description: string (optional) default is 'UTF8', defines the encoding used for the document returned by the web service.

parameters.name: fuzzy
parameters.description: float (optional) default is '1', defines the fuzziness of the search terms. float between 0 and 1. The search term is only applied to the name attribute.

parameters.name: east,west,north,south
parameters.description: float (optional) bounding box, only features within the box are returned

parameters.name: searchlang
parameters.description: string (optional) in combination with the name parameter, the search will only consider names in the specified language. Used for instance to query for IATA airport codes.

parameters.name: orderby
parameters.description: string (optional)[population,elevation,relevance] in combination with the name_startsWith, if set to 'relevance' than the result is sorted by relevance.

parameters.name: inclBbox
parameters.description: string (option) [true] include Bbox info, regardelss of style setting. (normally only included with style=FULL

parameters.name: postalcode
parameters.description: string ( postalcode or placename required) postal code

parameters.name: postalcode_startsWith
parameters.description: string the first characters or letters of a postal code

parameters.name: placename
parameters.description: string ( postalcode or placename required) all fields : placename,postal code, country, admin name ( Important: urlencoded utf8 )

parameters.name: placename_startsWith
parameters.description: string the first characters of a place name

parameters.name: country
parameters.description: string : country code, ISO-3166 (optional) Default is all countries. The country parameter may occur more than once, example: country=FR&country=GP

parameters.name: countryBias
parameters.description: string records from the countryBias are listed first

parameters.name: maxRows
parameters.description: integer (optional) the maximal number of rows in the document returned by the service. Default is 10

parameters.name: style
parameters.description: string SHORT , MEDIUM , LONG , FULL (optional) verbosity of returned xml document, default = MEDIUM

parameters.name: operator
parameters.description: string AND , OR (optional) the operator 'AND' searches for all terms in the placename parameter, the operator 'OR' searches for any term, default = AND

parameters.name: charset
parameters.description: string (optional) default is 'UTF8', defines the encoding used for the document returned by the web service.

parameters.name: isReduced
parameters.description: true or false (optional) default is 'false', when set to 'true' only the UK outer codes are returned. Attention: the default value on the commercial servers is currently set to 'true'. It will be changed later to 'false'.

parameters.name: east,west,north,south
parameters.description: float (optional) bounding box, only features within the box are returned
